1.Install LOCALHOST
2.2Install Node.js.
3.Click on the install.bat file which allows you to install the dependencies.
4.Create an application by connecting to the Developers Portal on the Discord site then activate the bot options via the Bot tab and retrieve the token.
5.At the bottom of the Bot tab page, enable the SERVER MEMBERS INTENT Server Members Instent
6.Invite your bot via the invite link via the OAuth2 tab.
7.Open the config.json file and enter the requested information.
8.In the .env file, enter your token.
9.Finally, to launch the bot, double-click on the start.bat file
If you have any questions or issues, open a comment in the GitHub Issues tab or message me on discord @L̶̶̶e̶̶̶r̶̶̶k̶̶̶i̶̶̶n̶#0564
